<seg id="82">VIES system</seg>
<seg id="83">In order to control the application of the claim for exemption from VAT in intra-Community delivery of goods, the system of exchange of information in the VAT sector was created within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="84">It includes an electronic system VIES, which allows tax administrators to check the Member States of the EU whether the supplier was entitled to free taxable performance from VAT and vice versa, whether the acquired goods acquired properly and taxed.</seg>
<seg id="85">The VIES information system is not centralized within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="86">Each Member State develops its own VIES system.</seg>
<seg id="87">National systems work on a common principle and are interconnected through the EU common communication network, so-called CCN (Common Communication Network; see the scheme below).</seg>
<seg id="88">In the Czech Republic, the VIES system was connected to an automated tax information system (hereinafter referred to as the “ADIS”), in Slovakia with the application program equipment of the tax information system (hereinafter referred to as “APV DIS”).</seg>
<seg id="89">These systems use financial or tax authorities as technical support for executive and management activities in managing taxes and fees.</seg>
<seg id="90">International administrative cooperation</seg>
<seg id="91">Through the international administrative cooperation, the tax administration receives information on tax entities, which would not be able to obtain itself without this cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="92">The main objective of the international administrative cooperation is to fight tax evasion and tax losses.</seg>
<seg id="93">According to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 each Member State sets out within the internal organisational structure of the central unit in the area of administrative cooperation between EU Member States in the administration of VAT, so-called. CLO (Central Liaison Office).</seg>
<seg id="94">In the Czech Republic it performs tasks arising from international cooperation The Ministry of Finance – Central Financial and Tax Directorate, where Department of International Cooperation was established in VAT administration (hereinafter referred to as “MF CLO”).</seg>
<seg id="95">The CLO function in Slovakia fulfills the Tax Directorate of Slovakia, Department of International Administrative Cooperation (hereinafter referred to as “DR CLO”).</seg>
<seg id="96">This department, among other things, communicate with foreign EU administrators, especially in the area of exchange of information within the VIES system, exchange of spontaneous information and information on the request of the EU tax administrators, coordination of multilateral (simultaneous) tax inspections, verification of tax identification numbers (hereinafter referred to as the “VAT n”) of persons registered for VAT in other EU Member States and communicate with the European Commission.</seg>
<seg id="97">In order to verify certain intra-community transactions or obtain further information relating to a specific tax entity, they send financial or tax authorities through the Ministry of Finance of CLO or DR CLO to the EU application for information.</seg>
<seg id="98">Through these applications, the information that can be used for the correct determination of VAT is obtained from the requested Member States.</seg>
<seg id="99">Applications for information are sent between CLO EU Member States in electronic form, using the standardized SCAC form.</seg>
