<seg id="40">The legal regulation in both countries is based on the regulations of the European Union governing this area, in particular: - Council Directive 92/12/EEC on general regulation, possession, movement and monitoring of products subject to consumer tax (hereinafter referred to as the “Directive 92/12/EEC”), - Council Regulation (EC) No 2073/2004 on administrative cooperation in the field of excise duty (hereinafter referred to as “Regulation No. 2073/2004”), - Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2719/92 on accompanying official document during the transport of products subject to consumer tax under the conditional exemption regime from excise duty (hereinafter referred to as “Regulation No. 2719/92”), - Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3649/92 on a simplified accompanying document for the movement of products subject to consumer tax released for domestic consumption in the sending Member State within the Community (</seg>
