<seg id="43">2.1 Movement of goods subject to excise duty in the regime of conditional exemption from tax between EU Member States</seg>
<seg id="44">The conditions of movement of goods subject to consumer tax in conditional exemption mode are governed by Directive 92/12/EEC in head III — Movement of goods Art. 15 to 20.</seg>
<seg id="45">According to these provisions, the transport of this goods may only be implemented by a legitimate warehouse, which means a natural or legal person authorized by the competent authorities of the Member State to produce, process, store, receive and send products subject to consumer tax.</seg>
<seg id="46">The recipient in another Member State may be a legitimate warehouse or an economic entity without the position of a legitimate composer who must not store or send these products in the regime of conditional exemption from tax.</seg>
<seg id="47">The authorised warehouse in the Czech Republic and Slovakia means the operator of the tax warehouse, the economic entity is a legitimate recipient for repeated or disposable receipt of products subject to excise duty.</seg>
<seg id="48">According to Directive 92/12/EEC, the transport of products subject to consumer tax in conditional exemption is possible only with accompanying document.</seg>
<seg id="49">The accompanying document is issued by the sender before the transport is started in four copies, unless the competent authorities sending the Member State require further execution.</seg>
<seg id="50">2.2 Procedure for initiation and termination of transport of goods in conditional liberation regime from tax between the Czech Republic and Slovakia</seg>
<seg id="51">Transport from the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="52">The procedure for the commencement of transport regulates the provisions of § 25 para. 3 of Act No. 353/2003 Coll., where, among others, it is said:</seg>
<seg id="53">“The operator of the tax warehouse is obliged to realise the customs office in front of the transport of selected products, which is a local tax warehouse, from which the transport should be initiated;</seg>
