<seg id="55">The Customs Office shall issue consent to the transport of selected products immediately after the condition of tax provision is fulfilled...”</seg>
<seg id="56">The Sender in the Czech Republic can start transporting all types of products subject to consumer tax only with the consent of the locally competent customs office.</seg>
<seg id="57">The Customs Office shall issue consent to the commencement of transport only if the tax amount attributed to the transported products is provided.</seg>
<seg id="58">The Sender is obliged to prepare a accompanying document in five copies before the transport is started.</seg>
<seg id="59">The accompanying document will indicate the customs office of the consent with the start of the transport.</seg>
<seg id="60">The execution No. 1 shall retain the sender, the execution of No.2, 3, and 4 shall submit the carrier to the carrier and the execution No. 5 shall retain the customs office permitting the transport.</seg>
<seg id="61">According to the Slovak legislation, the recipient will retain no 2 accompanying document in Slovakia. The preparation No. 3 and 4 confirm the receipt of the products and the two execution will submit the locally competent customs office.</seg>
<seg id="62">The preparation No. 3 confirmed by the customs authority sends the sender to the sender until 15th day of the month following the calendar month in which the products accepted.</seg>
