<seg id="191">6. Summary</seg>
<seg id="192">The cooperation of the SAO and the SAO SR allowed to compare the basic legislation governing the area of excise duty in both countries, the procedure of customs bodies of the Czech Republic and Slovakia during the start and termination of the transport of products in the regime of conditional exemption from tax between the two states, the registration of these transport and further comparison of the exchange of information between customs authorities within the framework of international cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="193">6.1 By comparing legislation governing the area of excise duty in the Czech Republic and Slovakia, differences were found:</seg>
<seg id="194">a) in the procedure of tax entities and tax administrators in the opening of the transport of products in the regime of conditional exemption from tax.</seg>
<seg id="195">The transport of the products in the condition of conditional exemption from tax may only be initiated by the tax entity in the Czech Republic with the consent of the tax administrator who will allow the start of transport under the conditions that the transported products have been provided tax of the tax amount attributed to them.</seg>
<seg id="196">The authorisation of the tax administrator is not subject to the commencement of the transport of products in the conditional exemption regime from Slovakia in Slovakia.</seg>
<seg id="197">In the audited period, the tax entity was obliged to notify the tax administrator of the commencement of transport of liabilities and tobacco products.</seg>
<seg id="198">Transport of mineral oils, beer and wine could start without informed the tax administrator about this fact.</seg>
<seg id="199">In 2006, the amendment to all excise tax laws was gradually adopted in Slovakia, according to which the sender of the goods in the condition of conditional exemption from the tax is obliged to send a copy of 1 parade document electronically or by fax to the customs office, which is locally relevant to the sender;</seg>
<seg id="200">b) within the deadlines for sending no 3 parade document.</seg>
<seg id="201">The recipient in the Czech Republic is obliged to send the execution no. 3 and 4 accompanying document to the verification administrator at the latest.</seg>
