<seg id="617">5. Conclusion</seg>
<seg id="618">The cooperation of both SAI on parallel audits of VAT management fulfilled the objectives set out in the SAO and BRH.</seg>
<seg id="619">Both SAI better met each other valid systems in these areas: • intra-Community transactions, • VAT risk management, especially when it comes to the selection of transactions with a tendency to risk, • assistance in debt recovery and • VAT control for large tax entities.</seg>
<seg id="620">Thanks to mutual cooperation, differences in the strategies of determining the cases of VAT fraud and differences in the above areas of VAT administration in the Czech Republic and Germany were revealed.</seg>
<seg id="621">The control findings were compared and proven practices were identified on their basis.</seg>
<seg id="622">In addition, both SAI hopes to become an impulse for stakeholders to start a discussion of approaches and strategies inside the Member States, among them at the European Commission level.</seg>
